# PHASE 2 — RAG Knowledge Pipeline

## 2.1 Objective

Give Bessie access to your organization's institutional knowledge — forecasting SOPs, GL-specific guidance, accounting policies, historical commentary — without bloating the system prompt or requiring code changes when knowledge is updated. Business users should be able to update knowledge by editing a Google Doc, with changes flowing automatically into Bessie's reasoning.

## 2.2 Why RAG Reduces Hallucinations

Without RAG, when Bessie encounters a question requiring business context (e.g. "why does GL 41200 Free Rent spike in Q1?"), she has two bad options: make something up, or say she doesn't know. With RAG, she retrieves the organization's actual explanation from your documented knowledge base and cites it. This is the most impactful single change for reducing hallucinations on domain-specific questions.

## 2.3 Architecture Decision: What RAG Covers

RAG handles **business knowledge and reasoning context**. It does NOT handle financial data (that stays in Yardi/Google Drive). This separation is critical:

| Layer | Managed by | RAG? |
|---|---|---|
| Raw financial data (actuals, budgets) | Yardi → Google Drive → Tool 6 | ❌ No |
| Calculated results (NOI, variances) | Tool 6 deterministic code | ❌ No |
| Business rules (how to forecast GL X) | RAG knowledge base | ✅ Yes |
| FP&A methodology (trailing avg logic) | RAG knowledge base | ✅ Yes |
| Historical commentary ("Q2 spike was due to...") | RAG knowledge base | ✅ Yes |
| Market benchmarks (CMHC) | HTTP Request Tool + RAG | ✅ Partial |

