# Future Scalability

## Power Automate Migration

| Capability | n8n today | Power Automate future |
|---|---|---|
| Excel formatting (CF, dropdowns) | ❌ SheetJS limitation | ✅ Office Scripts + Excel Online |
| SharePoint document store | ❌ Not available | ✅ Native |
| Teams notifications | ❌ Requires custom webhook | ✅ Native connector |
| Approval workflows (Power Automate Approvals) | ❌ Manual escalation | ✅ Native approval flows |
| Audit logging | Google Sheets | SharePoint List or Dataverse |

Migration recommendation: migrate the Excel generation step first (highest value), then the document store (enables SharePoint-native RAG), then the approval workflows.

## Yardi YDC Integration (Direct API)

Currently Bessie reads Yardi data via manually exported Excel files in Google Drive. Direct YDC integration eliminates the manual export step:

- Yardi Data Connect (YDC) provides REST APIs for GL data, rent roll, and budgets
- n8n can call YDC APIs directly via HTTP Request node
- Replace the 4 Google Drive file-reading branches in Tool 6 with 4 YDC API calls
- This enables real-time data (not export-lag dependent) and eliminates the manual upload workflow

**Pre-requisite:** YDC requires a Yardi subscription add-on and IT approval. Plan this as a Phase 4 item.

## Multi-Property Batch Mode

Currently Bessie runs one property at a time (chat-driven). A scheduled batch workflow can loop over all 7 properties:

```
[Schedule Trigger — quarterly]
        ↓
[Code: Load property list from config]
        ↓
[Loop over properties]
        ↓
[Call Tool 6 for each property]
        ↓ (after all complete)
[Call Tool 7 QA for each output]
        ↓
[Aggregate summary report → email/Teams]
```

This requires no changes to Tool 6 or the QA agent — just a wrapper loop.

